label.value: transferase activity, transferring phosphorus-containing groups

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

definition.value: Note that this term encompasses all kinase activities, as well as activities that transfer other phosphorus-containing groups such as diphosphate or nucleotides.

label.value: phosphotransferase activity, alcohol group as acceptor

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to an alcohol group (acceptor).

label.value: phosphotransferase activity, carboxyl group as acceptor

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to a carboxyl group (acceptor).

label.value: phosphotransferase activity, nitrogenous group as acceptor

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to a nitrogenous group (acceptor).

label.value: phosphotransferase activity, phosphate group as acceptor

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to a phosphate group (acceptor).

label.value: diphosphotransferase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a diphosphate group from one compound (donor) to a another (acceptor).

label.value: nucleotidyltransferase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a nucleotidyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: phosphotransferase activity, for other substituted phosphate groups

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a substituted phosphate group, other than diphosphate or nucleotidyl residues, from one compound (donor) to a another (acceptor).

label.value: phosphotransferase activity, paired acceptors

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of two phosphate groups from a donor, such as ATP, to two different acceptors.

label.value: transferase activity, transferring sulphur-containing groups

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a sulfur-containing group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: sulfurtransferase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of sulfur atoms from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: 3-mercaptopyruvate sulfurtransferase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: 3-mercaptopyruvate + cyanide = pyruvate + thiocyanate.

label.value: selenotransferase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a selenium-containing group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: hydrolase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of various bonds, e.g. C-O, C-N, C-C, phosphoric anhydride bonds, etc.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on ester bonds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any ester bond.

label.value: thiolester hydrolase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: RCO-SR' + H2O = RCOOH + HSR'. This reaction is the hydrolysis of a thiolester bond, an ester formed from a carboxylic acid and a thiol (i.e., RCO-SR'), such as that found in acetyl-coenzyme A.

label.value: phosphatase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a phosphoric monoester, releasing a phosphate.

label.value: triphosphoric monoester hydrolase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a triphosphoester to give a triphosphate group and a free hydroxyl group.

label.value: diphosphoric monoester hydrolase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a diphosphoester, releasing a diphosphate and a free hydroxyl group.

label.value: phosphoric triester hydrolase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a phosphoric triester.

label.value: exonuclease activity, active with either ribo- or deoxyribonucleic acids and producing 5'-phosphomonoesters

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of ester linkages within nucleic acids by removing nucleotide residues from the 3' or 5' end to yield 5' phosphomonoesters.

definition.value: Note that this activity can catalyze cleavage of DNA or RNA.

label.value: exonuclease activity, active with either ribo- or deoxyribonucleic acids and producing 3'-phosphomonoesters

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of ester linkages within nucleic acids by removing nucleotide residues from the 3' or 5' end to yield 3' phosphomonoesters.

definition.value: Note that this activity can catalyze cleavage of DNA or RNA.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on glycosyl bonds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any glycosyl bond.

label.value: hydrolase activity, hydrolyzing N-glycosyl compounds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any N-glycosyl bond.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on ether bonds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any ether or thioether bond, -O- or -S- respectively.

label.value: trialkylsulfonium hydrolase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a thioether bond, -S-.

label.value: ether hydrolase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of an ether bond, -O-.

label.value: dipeptidase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a dipeptide.

label.value: cysteine-type carboxypeptidase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a single C-terminal amino acid residue from a polypeptide chain by a mechanism in which the sulfhydryl group of a cysteine residue at the active center acts as a nucleophile.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any carbon-nitrogen bond, C-N, with the exception of peptide bonds.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds, in linear amides

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any non-peptide carbon-nitrogen bond in a linear amide.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds, in cyclic amides

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any non-peptide carbon-nitrogen bond in a cyclic amide.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds, in linear amidines

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any non-peptide carbon-nitrogen bond in a linear amidine, a compound of the form R-C(=NH)-NH2.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds, in cyclic amidines

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any non-peptide carbon-nitrogen bond in a cyclic amidine, a compound of the form R-C(=NH)-NH2.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds, in nitriles

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any non-peptide carbon-nitrogen bond in a nitrile, a compound containing the cyano radical, -CN.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on acid anhydrides

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid anhydride.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on acid anhydrides, in phosphorus-containing anhydrides

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid anhydride which contains phosphorus.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on acid anhydrides, in sulfonyl-containing anhydrides

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid anhydride which contains a sulfonyl group, -SO2-.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on acid carbon-carbon bonds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid carbon-carbon bond.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on acid carbon-carbon bonds, in ketonic substances

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid carbon-carbon bond in a ketonic substance, a substance containing a keto (C=O) group.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on acid halide bonds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid halide bond.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on acid phosphorus-nitrogen bonds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid phosphorus-nitrogen bond.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on acid sulfur-nitrogen bonds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid sulfur-nitrogen bond.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on acid carbon-phosphorus bonds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid carbon-phosphorus bond.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on acid sulfur-sulfur bonds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid sulfur-sulfur bond.

label.value: lyase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of C-C, C-O, C-N and other bonds by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, or conversely adding a group to a double bond. They differ from other enzymes in that two substrates are involved in one reaction direction, but only one in the other direction. When acting on the single substrate, a molecule is eliminated and this generates either a new double bond or a new ring.

label.value: carbon-carbon lyase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of C-C bonds by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, or conversely adding a group to a double bond.

label.value: carboxy-lyase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the nonhydrolytic addition or removal of a carboxyl group to or from a compound.

label.value: aldehyde-lyase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of a C-C bond in a molecule containing a hydroxyl group and a carbonyl group to form two smaller molecules, each being an aldehyde or a ketone.

label.value: oxo-acid-lyase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of a C-C bond by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, of a 3-hydroxy acid.
